 \dfrac{1}{x^2+1}\dfrac{dy}{dx} + xy = 3
y(0) = 0
 \dfrac{dy}{dx} +(x^3+x)y = 3x^2 +3
r(x) = e^{(\int x^3+x) dx} = e^{\dfrac{x^4}{4}+ \dfrac{x^2}{2}}
ye^{\dfrac{x^4}{4}+ \dfrac{x^2}{2}} = \int (3x^2+3)e^{\dfrac{x^4}{4}+ \dfrac{x^2}{2}} dx
Edit
y(0) = 0
y =\dfrac{ \int_{0}^{x} (3t^2+3)e^{\dfrac{t^4}{4}+ \dfrac{t^2}{2}} dt}{e^{\dfrac{x^4}{4}+ \dfrac{x^2}{2}}}
